article.description: Kevon Harris scored 22 points as Stephen F. Austin defeated Arkansas State 76-57 on Saturday.
article.headline: Harris leads Stephen F. Austin over Arkansas St. 76-57
article.linkText: Harris leads Stephen F. Austin over Arkansas St. 76-57
article.story: JONESBORO, Ark. -- Kevon Harris scored 22 points as Stephen F. Austin defeated Arkansas State 76-57 on Saturday. Gavin Kensmil added 20 points and 15 rebounds for the Lumberjacks (6-1), who are on a roll after defeating No. 1 Duke 85-83 in overtime on Tuesday. Cameron Johnson had eight points and six rebounds. Caleb Fields had 18 points, seven rebounds and six assists for the Red Wolves (5-2), whose four-game winning streak was broken. Canberk Kus added 16 points and eight rebounds. Jerry Johnson Jr. had 10 points. Marquis Eaton had 1 point despite entering the matchup as the Red Wolves' second leading scorer at 12 points per game. Stephen F. Austin plays Arlington Baptist at home on Monday. Arkansas State faces Nebraska Omaha at home on Tuesday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
